;; Regression: (at vec idxvec) builds a RAY_LIST result of the index length
;; and fills it element by element.  When an element lookup errors mid-loop,
;; the cleanup path used to release the already-filled prefix AND then
;; ray_release the whole result (double-freeing the prefix and reading the
;; uninitialised tail) → crash in ray_release_owned_refs.  Found by the eval
;; fuzz target with (at [true] [false]) (a bool index is not an integer, so
;; the very first element errors, leaving the whole result uninitialised).
;; Now it errors cleanly.
;; A bool index vector makes the very first element error, leaving the whole
;; result list uninitialised — the case that crashed.
(at [true] [false]) !- type
(at [1 2 3] [true]) !- type

;; Valid integer indexing still works.
(at [10 20 30] [0 2]) -- [10 30]
(at [10 20 30] 1) -- 20
